<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have the rag on • lose one’s rag</xh5><p> <i>have the rag on</i>—(sl., also: have the rags on) have one’s menstrual period: His wife always either <u>had the rag on</u> or had a headache every time he wanted to have a little fun.</p><p> <i>lose one’s rag</i>—(sl.) lose one’s temper: Allison <u>lost his rag</u> with me over two goals by Leicester’s Mike Stringfellow.</p> </entry>
